CipherVault
A local file vault for your desktop. CipherVault lets you protect sensitive files behind a master password — everything stored on disk is encrypted, nothing is sent anywhere.
Features
Master password setup
 — on first launch you create a password; all subsequent access requires it
Strong key derivation
 — uses 
 with a random salt to turn your password into an encryption key
AES-GCM encryption
 — every file you import is encrypted with 
 before it touches disk
Local SQLite storage
 — file metadata and audit records live in a single database file on your machine
Audit log
 — every login attempt, import, export, and deletion is recorded with a timestamp
JavaFX dashboard
 — a clean desktop UI for managing your vault day to day
`PBKDF2WithHmacSHA256``AES/GCM/NoPadding`
